			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Swarming?? FORGET IT!!<a name="17519"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 04 6:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
I've been reading all the info on this board and others about swarm kiting.  Seems like a great way to get quick experience, is supposedly safer than AoE kiting, quicker than chant kiting etc. Sounds great, I'm all for it
<br />

<br />
Ok, so I'm a 53 bard, and the swarming options for experience are pretty limited.  Tried PoN but nothing in EQ is more camped.  Seems like everyone recommends the flies in PoD, so I head down there.  Figure I'll start small so I grab 4 flies off the first island by the big rock.  I drag em over to the rock and start circling around trying to bunch them up.  This works reasonably well, and through all the powers of my concentration, I can keep from getting killed.
<br />

<br />
Then you throw in charming a target, picking a new target and attacking, watching your pets hps so you can break charm in time, chanting 3-4 songs, all this while your still spinning in nice little circles - Forget it!
<br />

<br />
I don't see how you people do this.  I was successful in killing 3 flies on three separate attempts, then would have a slight misstep, get chain stunned and die. Fun.
<br />

<br />
Is there something I'm missing here or am I just a total gimp?  I don't see how anyone can do this, particularly with a large swarm where you get hit once and die.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
