				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming?? FORGET IT!!<a name="17524"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 04 6:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>hehe I've been there, done that... you did far better than I when I started!
<br />

<br />
I'll just say, sit down to a piano... yeah I know, you don't play... Now play Beethoven.  Come on... Da da da da... you know the music.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />  
<br />

<br />
Seriously, Swarming is HARD. Don't let veteran swarmers tell you otherwise. They have just forgotten their troubles early on.  It takes PRACTICE, PRACTICE, and MORE PRACTICE!  Yep, you will die, but keep at it. Soon you will have it down pat!
<br />

<br />
One suggestion is to make your circles bigger to keep you farther from the swarm.  Also, when you are taking your swarm to your charm'd pet and mob he's attacking, try for a straight line, directly over your pet so the swarm trains your pet.  Also proximity aggroing is good to not have any aggro on your swarm.  Finally, a UI that allows you swap out instruments if you are having troubles getting charm to stick (using my flute meant the world to me).
<br />

<br />
Good luck and hang in there, it will become second nature!
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
