			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming?? FORGET IT!!<a name="17567"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 2:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well 2 advices for you: 
<br />
- don't try to learn swarming at flies, esp. if you aren't used to running around in 3rd person view. If you are new to swarming AND 3rd person view &quot;action&quot;, maybe go to spirocs in TD. There I learned swarming and moving in 3rd person view. The terrain is very simple there...perfectly flat and no trees and stuff. that helps. No good exp at your level, but do that for an hour or 2 and you should have it down.
<br />
- set up 3rd person view before you pull mobs. Go to where you want to swarm later (if possible, but usually it is), set up the 3rd person view you want to use..go back to 1st person view and pull your mobs. I found the setup of 3rd person view one of the most important thngs.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
