		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming?? FORGET IT!!<a name="17585"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 8:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been swarming since about level thirty (yes, it can be done!)  And no, its not easy.  I started with hill giants in Frontier Mountains.  Man, people didn't like me pulling more than half the fort for myself.  Never killed anyone with a train though!  Later I went to frost giants and dire wolves in Great Divide near the EW zone, and then after that took my gig to the giant fort in EW.  God knows how many times I died when I first started, but once I got going, it all paid off.
<br />
There are a few little handy things I've picked up along the way, but the most important thing I've found is to make sure you've set up a key to switch between the last two targets.  It doesn't have a default key, so you have to do it yourself.  Its made my life a bajillion times easier!  This way its much easier to keep track of which mob in your swarm is your pet, in case charm breaks really fast or whatever.  I also use it to actually start the swarm, so once I've got it all coming at me, I just hit my switch target key and click attack.
<br />
In PoD specifically, because the terrain is kind of weird, I also use my Singing Steel Boots for a little lev action, to keep it all stable.  This way I'm not running up and down hills and whatnot.  Also makes pulling a big swarm from the back of the peninsula much easier too.
<br />
Personally, I've never used 3rd person view.  I have forever and always used 1st person view with no problems.  I've always been able to stay well ahead of my mobs and still be able to target and everything just fine by turning around.  *shrug*  So I don't think its necessary to use 3rd person.
<br />
In the end, don't give up, because its a really fast and effective way to get xp for when you have to solo.  Even at 64 I'm making good xp swarming with the 64 song on Plane of Mischief yard trash!  I've gone from 0% to 45% in only a few hours there.  Not bad, I'd say.
<br />
If you have any questions or anything, feel free to send me a tell and I'll help however I can<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
Myrmion
<br />
64 Bard, Xegony</span></td>
