			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming?? FORGET IT!!<a name="17633"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 12:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a favorite spot to Swarm / Chant Kite. While the exp per kill is nothing compared to PoD, it is relatively easy and caster free. I have gotten decent exp even at 53 and to this day at 57, I still run back there for those half hour time slots. I have a boy who's almost 3 and a 9 month old, so play time is limited, and often sporatic during teething times. I can easily swarm and camp this spot at any given moment.
<br />

<br />
Burning Woods!
<br />

<br />
One of the least populated zones in EQ. If there are one or two people in the zone, they are usually camping the Giant Fort. But the Giants have a bunch of HP, require wider circles and you may get a Sarnak caster in your swarm or even a Wurm. Skip the giants, they also run and can poof at 20%.
<br />

<br />
Do the hornets! 
<br />

<br />
Enter Burning Woods from the Dreadlands. Hug the zone wall to the left until you see the Hive. From the Hive, turn back towards the Dreadlands zone and run up the hill to a wide open Plateau. This is where you can swarm with relative ease.
<br />

<br />
Mem all your Chants except for Flame (everything in BW resists it) including Fufil's. Mem your 39 Charm and your cancel magic. Mem 2.5 minute Selo's. Set up your hotkeys.
<br />
You may want to use a non-damage like OOS for pulling, so that your pet can secure aggro.
<br />

<br />
Have tracking ready so you can pick your targets. 
<br />

<br />
Run around and grab as many as you can with either aggro (very small radius) or I use fufils. Get anywhere from 4-15 (my max so far) chasing you. They are slow, so don't out run them. Keep just enough ahead so you can pull from hornet to hornet wth ease. Once you get your swarm, run a few wide circles, slowly tightening them up. Your best bet for a pet is a Scoriae Hornet or Ember Hornet. They have the best damage output. Have them sit to gain aggro, or sick them on something. The Ash Hornets (green to light blue @ 57) drop fast, followed by the Cinder (green to light blue @ 57), then Ember (light blue to dark blue @ 57)and last is Scoriae (dark blue @57). If you can successfully get you Scoriae pet down to 30%, then simply chant away to finish it. These MoBs never run, unless feared and have relatively low hp to most dark blue MoBs I've seen. I get 1% real exp for every 2 decent size swarms at 57. Each swarm takes 1 minute to gather (rarely have to wait for spawns as they'll come to you, just go to hive if you run out). Then each swarm takes 5-10 minutes to drop. I have grouped in Plane of Innovation and Plane of Disease and have gained the same exp in 3x the time. The soloing in PoD has seemingly brought me the same exp to time killing ratio and, in my humble opinion, is very dangerous for a casual player such as myself. 
<br />

<br />
The greatest bit being, if you have to go afk for any period of time, you simply go sit and hide at the zone wall. I have changed many a diaper and rocked many a baby without having to log. 
<br />

<br />
Each hornet will drop 5sp to 5pp. The wings sell for 3pp+ at vendors. I usually get a couple of decent gems, jade rings and some spell drops which I sell in bazaar. I seem to always leave with apx 300pp in cash and vendor sellable goods. 
<br />

<br />
They also don't hit terribly hard(max 115) and are a great place to pratice your swarming technique. 
<br />

<br />
Just my 2cp worth!
<br />

<br />
Wiladancer, the Evernewb bard from Torv!</span></td>
