			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming?? FORGET IT!!<a name="17665"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 3:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Lots of good advice here and my suggestion is to follow it in this order:
<br />

<br />
1) learn on safe stuff.  It wont take long to get the hang of what you need to do and how much room you need.  Any of the places mentioned for lvl 40s to swarm are good.  Hornets are very good for this because they are slow, stupid and dont have much of an agro radus.
<br />

<br />
2) use the F1 (target self and pet target) key.  I also use f8 to get a target, then charm and f8 to get the target for my pet - all while running backwards because I am a 3rd person klutz.  Selos helps but Sow works fine you just need to judge the distances which comes with experience.
<br />

<br />
3) If you are luck you pet is being pounded by the swarm, if not loop around the now closing mob and run straight through your pet (hit F1 twice to get your pet targeted).  Repeat as necessary however I would caution against doing this if 1 or 2 are following you because the rest of teh mob will beat on you as you run through your pet and that could be bad.
<br />

<br />
4) if you dont have lev, jump over your pet.  I have gotten hung up on them and it hurt.
<br />

<br />
5) It takes a while to get the timing down for inviz.  All the inviz clickies will make your swarming faster but you will run out of mana quicker.
<br />

<br />
6) break charm and chant your target down and start over.
<br />

<br />
7) Looting can be dangerous - sometimes (flys and toilers are good at this) looting can draw agro and nothing is worse than getting that nodrop window when a couple of mobs are taking advantage of you while you are bent over.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Tin.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
