				<td colspan="2"><span>Thanks for all the good info here guys, it really helped.  I decided to try the big open area near the entrance to Dulak, and had much greater success.  I first swarmed the mobs just standing around in the courtyard, then went around the buildings picking up some of the higher level mobs.  Making bigger circles and running on a flat surface made all the difference, and I was able to improve my timing and coordination.
<br />

<br />
I can now see that it can be done, but I'm wondering about just how good the xps can be.  In an hour, I took out maybe 25 mobs and received approximately 7% experience.  Granted, many of the mobs here are light blue, but it seems like in order to get better experience I'll be forced to head to the planes, if not now at least in a few more levels.  I don't know if the risk-reward is worth it after my experience with the flies.  
<br />

<br />
My main is a 65 Shaman, and I've 2 boxed my Bard through much of his career.  At this point, with the Bard tanking, meleeing and chanting and the Shaman handling haste, slows, heals, pet, dots etc, the experience seems better and the risk is less.  I've recently spent time in the Mines of Nurga and generally get .5-1.5% per kill with kills taking ~ 2 minutes.  There will probably come a time when the Bard is no longer able to handle tanking mobs, particularly with Shaman heals, but he's not there yet.
<br />

<br />
So, I still don't think that swarming is for me, but I'll hold onto my gazughi (sp?) ring and see what happens<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />
Anyone have an opinion on which is better xp - swarming, grouping or my 2 box setup?  I get groups when I can, but sometimes I just like to log for a few minutes and accomplish something.
