				<td colspan="2"><span>Swarming is an acquired taste if you ask me.  Enough has already been said on the subject, but I just thought I'd add my experiences.  In my enitre 65 levels of playing a bard, I've swarmed....ONCE!  And I didn't like it, so I didn't do it.  Simple as that.  If it's not your thing, don't worry...there's so many choices of style play with a bard that you don't have to feel guilty or stupid or something for not swarming.  Grouping is what eq was made for, and thus my main is the most group oriented class in the game ;)
<br />

<br />
What I'm saying is everyone here is right.  Don't swarm if you don't want to.  If you like to solo, do it!  But if you don't, as good as our class is at soloing, it's even better at grouping <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />   Swarming is very viable exp, and prolly great for when you don't have time/patience to find a group, but it's definitely not a necessity.
