			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarming?? FORGET IT!!<a name="18047"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 2:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At 53 I spent a lot of time in Maiden's Eye doing the toilers there back behind the fort that's by the DSP entrance.  They aggro easy, they repop fast, and you will get a ton of them.  (Usually had 10-20 chasing me, with lots of room.)
<br />

<br />
I used to use the clicky ring, but I got tired of it, because you have to target yourself to use it, which is a major hassle.  At first I didn't like swarming because there were so many things that could go wrong.  I mean chant kiting... just push 1-2-3-4 and circle.  I use GameVoice to play the twist, so all I have to do is steer!
<br />

<br />
Swarming is a lot more involved, I won't argue that.  But I've really streamlined it now, and I'm very fast at it.  A kill every 1-2 minutes now, and I get 1-1.5% experience for those kills (56 @ PoNightmare).
<br />

<br />
Lineup - fire/poison/ice/disease chants, invis, charm, selo's, and an empty slot.  I keep heal usually, because I might get careless and get hit, and this way I can heal up without zoning or making a crazy sit-n-mem attempt at under 50%.
<br />

<br />
ESDF is my movement, A is target nearest, and X is toggle last 2 targets.
<br />

<br />
1-4 is my chants, 5 is invis, 6 is charm, and 7 is pet attack, 8 is speed.  I can just reach the pet attack if I stretch my hand, which is good, I don't want to do it on accident.
<br />

<br />
Playing speed most of the time, I round up the mobs, target nearest and charm, target nearest and attack.  Turn on speedsong and toggle back to my pet.  That's it, now I just kite around an stragglers that won't stick to the pet (happens from time to time) till the pet gets to the invis point.  Usually that's about 30%, 20% if there's not many left.  Start playing invis song (I have my epic, which is nice, but otherwise, kite with your Wind and equip Percussion for the kill, it's not that bad) and then chant it down.
<br />

<br />
Now the part I do to make things just a little faster:  Push X, and target the mob your last pet was on.  I don't charm it, I need to make the most of my charm, and that means taking out a pet with 100% if possible.  I target nearest for a fresh mob, charm it, then push X to get that wounded one again.  Sic pet, turn on speed, toggle back to pet, and get the pack on them.  I periodically push X to check on the one I'm killing.
<br />

<br />
Eventually, it will get pretty darned low, so you just chant it down.  If you just charm a mob and sic it on a random one in the pack, a few will eventually keep chasing you no matter what you do.  This way you're much more likely to keep everything on your pet.
<br />

<br />
I really learned a lot about chant kiting in Maiden's Eye though, where I had a horde of mobs to mess with, and very low risk.  And if you get bored, those toilers melt fast to a good chant kite, too.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
