				<td colspan="2"><span>A pet trick I use to use as a mage, (Back in my lazy days) was to have my pet attack a target and while he was beating on that one target a second mob and say pet attack, then a third and say pet attack. . . .this would automatically send my pet after the next target when the previous target bit the dust.  
<br />

<br />
So try letting your pet attack a weakened (DoT'd) mob while you gather the rest of your swarm, but include a pet attack on each one, so as you kite them he will move from one to another as you both win the fights. . .
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
