				<td colspan="2"><span>For good exp and a nice spot to learn keep trying for the Nightstalkers camp in PoN. It is overcamped because druids can survive there but I have gone back a few times in the last few months and found it empty for my druid to level on. Pkus the gem drops are nice. Can make a few k while swarming there easy.
<br />

<br />
The stalkers only hit for a max of around 300 and there is little or no risk of any adds. If for some reason you get trained then just run to zone and they all come back.
<br />

<br />
I personally swarm and always ahve in 1st person, I do alot of spinning though and people watching in game tend to get sick just being near me.
<br />

<br />
One big thing to remember, always have a hotkey that toggles between you and the last mob that you had targeted, and a separate one that toggles between your last 2 targets. Then save up for the goblin inst cast invis ring and go to town.
<br />

<br />
It does take alot of practice and patience to learn though, but after a while you will barely watdch the screen. h*ll, I bound in PoT just so I could take out a drum and spend raid corpse runs swarming in PoN.</span></td>
